==English==

===Verb===
{{en-verb|make<,,made> known}}

# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[announce]] (some [[information]]) generally.
#: {{ux|en|The decision was '''made known''' when it appeared on the evening news.}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|year=1960|month=December|title=Talking of Trains: Tube trains from Derby|journal=Trains Illustrated|page=706|text=This was announced in October when details of a £4 million order for car bodies and bogies to complete the Central and Piccadilly Line's rolling stock renewal programmes with 619 more "1959 Stock" cars were '''made known'''.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[disclose]] (a [[secret]]).
#: {{ux|en|I wouldn't '''make''' this '''known''' to anyone else, if I were you.}}

